
[1]decrepitate

   DECREPITATE, v.t. [L. To break or burst, to crackle.] To roast or
   calcine in a strong heat, with a continual bursting or crackling of the
   substance; as, to decrepitate salt.

   DECREPITATE, v.i. To crackle, as salts when roasting.
